A Biblepay wallet is as simple as a single pairing of a Biblepay address with its corresponding Biblepay private key. Such a wallet has been generated for you in your web browser and is displayed above.

To safeguard this wallet you must print or otherwise record the Biblepay address and private key. It is important to make a backup copy of the private key and store it in a safe location. This site does not have knowledge of your private key. If you leave/refresh the site or press the "Generate New Address" button then a new private key will be generated and the previously displayed private key will not be retrievable. Your Biblepay private key should be kept a secret. Whomever you share the private key with has access to spend all the Biblepays associated with that address. If you print your wallet then store it in a zip lock bag to keep it safe from water. Treat a paper wallet like cash.

Add funds to this wallet by instructing others to send Biblepays to your Biblepay address.

Check your balance by going to the block explorer and entering your Biblepay address.

Your Biblepay Private Key is a unique secret number that only you know. It can be encoded in a number of different formats. Below we show the Biblepay Address and Public Key that corresponds to your Private Key as well as your Private Key in the most popular encoding formats (WIF, WIFC, HEX, B64).

Biblepay stores public keys in compressed format. The client now also supports import and export of private keys with importprivkey/dumpprivkey.
